flowchart TB
    accTitle: AWS Public Change Alerting processing flow
    accDescr: Approved public AWS feeds and an immutable configuration release enter deterministic processing. Route-scoped candidates are stored in DynamoDB, dispatched through SQS FIFO, and delivered to Slack with recovery state retained in DynamoDB.

    subgraph Inputs["Approved inputs"]
        direction LR
        Feeds["AWS RSS and Atom feeds"]
        Release["Immutable configuration and inventory release"]
    end

    subgraph Decisioning["Deterministic candidate generation"]
        direction LR
        Watcher["Feed watcher"] --> Normalize["Normalize, coalesce, and track revisions"]
        Normalize --> Matcher["Service and risk matcher"]
        Matcher --> Routes["Profile and route mapping"]
        Routes --> Outbox["DynamoDB candidates and durable outbox"]
    end

    subgraph Delivery["Durable Slack delivery"]
        direction LR
        Dispatcher["Outbox dispatcher"] --> Queue["SQS FIFO by Slack destination"]
        Queue --> Worker["Slack delivery worker"]
        Worker --> Slack["Slack channel"]
        Reconciler["Recovery reconciler"]
    end

    Feeds --> Watcher
    Release --> Watcher
    Release --> Matcher
    Outbox --> Dispatcher
    Worker -->|"Known or unknown outcome"| Outbox
    Reconciler --> Outbox
